WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.101 --> 00:00:02.537
<i>Previously on</i> R.J. Decker...

2
00:00:02.670 --> 00:00:04.304
<i>- </i> <i>What are you wearing?</i>
<i>- </i> Excuse me?

3
00:00:04.438 --> 00:00:06.273
Change your shirt
and meet me at the address
I'm about to send you.

4
00:00:06.406 --> 00:00:07.909
Who needs you
to change your shirt?

5
00:00:08.041 --> 00:00:10.812
Wish. Yeah. he might have
a new client for me.

6
00:00:10.945 --> 00:00:13.046
<i>Welcome to the humble abode</i>
<i>of the Carter family.</i>

7
00:00:13.180 --> 00:00:15.349
That's Holden.
He may have relapsed.

8
00:00:15.482 --> 00:00:17.317
R.J..
Holden has been found.

9
00:00:17.451 --> 00:00:18.720
Holden was about
to blow the whistle.

10
00:00:18.853 --> 00:00:21.221
He was willing to go up
against his own father.

11
00:00:21.355 --> 00:00:23.223
Holden wasn't supposed to die.

12
00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:25.292
<i>The plan was only</i>
<i>to discredit him.</i>

13
00:00:26.059 --> 00:00:29.664
- Still think it was me.
- It was not you.

14
00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:38.305
<i>Of course.</i>
<i>I'll have to notify the police.</i>

15
00:00:38.438 --> 00:00:39.908
<i>This is a case for Homicide.</i>

16
00:00:40.708 --> 00:00:41.843
<i>Homicide?</i>

17
00:00:41.976 --> 00:00:44.077
<i>I don't think</i>
<i>you fully understand. Bigelow.</i>

18
00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:46.714
<i>You've been murdered.</i>

19
00:00:46.848 --> 00:00:48.048
R.J.. is that you?

20
00:00:48.181 --> 00:00:49.249
Yeah.

21
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:51.118
Are you alone?

22
00:00:51.251 --> 00:00:52.554
Yes. very.

23
00:00:52.687 --> 00:00:55.355
Aw. no love connection?

24
00:00:55.957 --> 00:00:57.457
No. I wasn't her type.

25
00:00:57.592 --> 00:00:59.694
Dude. you're everybody's type.

26
00:01:01.495 --> 00:01:03.631
Maybe you could've worn
a nicer shirt.

27
00:01:03.765 --> 00:01:06.534
Yeah. or my prison blues.

28
00:01:06.668 --> 00:01:08.937
Thought my criminal record
might be a deal-breaker.

29
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:11.438
but it turns out she asked
Mauricio to set us up

30
00:01:11.573 --> 00:01:13.140
because she only dates felons.

31
00:01:13.708 --> 00:01:15.108
-Creepy.
-Yeah.

32
00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:17.144
But doesn't that
make you her type?

33
00:01:17.277 --> 00:01:22.717
Apparently
I'm not felonious enough.
She likes the repeat offenders.

34
00:01:23.918 --> 00:01:26.788
Okay. maybe when it comes
to matchmakers.

35
00:01:26.921 --> 00:01:30.357
we can do better
than our old pals
from Apalachee.

36
00:01:30.490 --> 00:01:31.960
I'm sorry. what? W-Who's we?

37
00:01:32.092 --> 00:01:34.629
The algorithms
for the dating apps
are. like. insane now.

38
00:01:34.762 --> 00:01:37.197
I can help you poke
around online tomorrow.
try to find the right one.

39
00:01:37.331 --> 00:01:40.133
Algorithms? I think I'd rather
go back to prison.

40
00:01:41.201 --> 00:01:44.038
And why are you so determined
to fix me up all of a sudden?

41
00:01:44.171 --> 00:01:47.642
Just trying
to help you make better
choices. that's all.

42
00:01:48.442 --> 00:01:50.177
Better than what?

43
00:01:50.310 --> 00:01:54.716
I saw you having drinks
with Emi Ochoa at F.M. Station.
and you looked friendly.

44
00:01:55.617 --> 00:01:57.417
It's not what you think.

45
00:01:57.552 --> 00:01:59.854
We were married. okay?
I know what you look like
when you want to have sex.

46
00:01:59.988 --> 00:02:02.456
Emi Ochoa and I
are not sleeping together.

47
00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:04.993
We're not. She feels bad
about what happened.
She wants to...

48
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:06.493
she wants to make up for it.

49
00:02:06.628 --> 00:02:08.529
And how exactly
does one make up
for perjuring oneself

50
00:02:08.663 --> 00:02:10.064
and sending
an innocent person to prison?

51
00:02:10.197 --> 00:02:12.100
She brought me a case
last week. It worked out.

52
00:02:12.232 --> 00:02:14.468
We went out for a drink
to celebrate. That's it.

53
00:02:14.602 --> 00:02:17.204
I'm fine.
Everything's fine. okay?

54
00:02:18.072 --> 00:02:21.776
So. if you'll excuse me.
I have an early meeting
with a client tomorrow.

55
00:02:21.909 --> 00:02:23.911
I'm not going to sleep
with him either.

56
00:02:28.783 --> 00:02:31.719
Okay. Here's Louise
on her way to yoga.

57
00:02:31.853 --> 00:02:34.122
Playing mah-jongg at the club.

58
00:02:35.657 --> 00:02:38.158
Buying groceries. Bob...

59
00:02:40.662 --> 00:02:42.597
As much as I'd like
to keep taking your money.

60
00:02:42.730 --> 00:02:44.032
I've been following
your wife for a week.

61
00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:47.001
I have seen nothing that
tells me she's cheating on you.

62
00:02:47.969 --> 00:02:50.303
Look at Louise. Now look at me.

63
00:02:50.838 --> 00:02:53.407
She is at least a nine.
I am a five.

64
00:02:53.541 --> 00:02:55.977
and that's when
my psoriasis isn't acting up.

65
00:02:56.577 --> 00:02:59.080
I should've known better
than to think that
I could keep her happy.

66
00:02:59.212 --> 00:03:02.482
Are you sure
this whole affair thing
isn't just all in your head?

67
00:03:02.617 --> 00:03:03.818
I mean. are you sure?

68
00:03:04.952 --> 00:03:07.722
You see these earrings?
I didn't buy those for her.

69
00:03:08.623 --> 00:03:11.826
I checked her credit card
receipts. She didn't buy
them for herself.

70
00:03:11.959 --> 00:03:13.193
And when I asked her about it.

71
00:03:13.326 --> 00:03:15.530
she said that they were gifts
from her mother.

72
00:03:15.663 --> 00:03:18.365
but. uh. I-I know
that she's lying. I...

73
00:03:21.234 --> 00:03:26.607
I love her. Mr. Decker.
so much. and I need
to know what's going on.

74
00:03:26.741 --> 00:03:30.310
Because if I know
what's going on.
maybe I can fix it.

75
00:03:30.912 --> 00:03:32.914
Maybe I can make her
love me again.

76
00:05:51.185 --> 00:05:53.321
Hey. Bob.

77
00:05:53.453 --> 00:05:55.488
<i>I've been thinking.</i>
<i>Maybe you're right. Maybe</i>
<i>the affair is all in my head.</i>

78
00:05:55.623 --> 00:05:59.694
Bob. do you know anything
about a-a storage locker
on 19th Street?

79
00:06:00.294 --> 00:06:02.395
<i>No. why? Did Louise go</i>
<i>to a storage locker?</i>

80
00:06:02.530 --> 00:06:03.931
<i>Is that where you are now?</i>

81
00:06:04.599 --> 00:06:07.602
No. I'm in front
of a house on Palmetto.
She just went inside.

82
00:06:07.735 --> 00:06:09.804
<i>Does it have a fountain</i>
<i>in front with pink flamingos?</i>

83
00:06:09.937 --> 00:06:11.839
Yeah. it does.

84
00:06:11.973 --> 00:06:14.374
<i>Son of a...</i>
<i>That's the Howards' house. She</i>
<i>must be there to meet Preston.</i>

85
00:06:14.508 --> 00:06:15.710
Okay. who's Preston?

86
00:06:15.843 --> 00:06:17.410
<i>We know him and his wife</i>
<i>from the club.</i>

87
00:06:17.545 --> 00:06:19.580
<i>He and Louise both played</i>
<i>in the pickleball tournament.</i>

88
00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:22.449
Okay. Bob. listen to me.
Everything's gonna be okay.

89
00:06:22.583 --> 00:06:25.887
Deep breath and repeat
after me. okay? Everything...

90
00:06:26.020 --> 00:06:26.954
<i>Everything...</i>

91
00:06:27.088 --> 00:06:28.689
...is gonna be--

92
00:06:30.091 --> 00:06:31.525
<i>Mr. Decker.</i>
<i>what was that?</i>

93
00:06:32.526 --> 00:06:37.365
<i>Mr. Decker. can you hear me?</i>
<i>Mr. Decker. are you there?</i>

94
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:52.513
Fire marshal says
it's looking like an accident.

95
00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:55.448
There was a gas leak
somewhere inside. then a spark.

96
00:06:55.583 --> 00:06:57.952
Happens sometimes
in these old houses that
haven't converted to electric.

97
00:06:58.085 --> 00:06:59.387
What about bodies?

98
00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:01.756
One. Badly burned.
so no ID yet.

99
00:07:01.889 --> 00:07:03.257
It's got to be
my client's wife.

100
00:07:03.391 --> 00:07:05.393
I saw her go inside
right before it happened.

101
00:07:05.526 --> 00:07:07.528
Respectfully.
I'm a homicide detective.

102
00:07:07.662 --> 00:07:10.264
-not a tragic
accident detective.
-Yeah. I get it. I...

103
00:07:10.398 --> 00:07:13.000
Unless you're thinking
the fire marshal has it wrong.

104
00:07:13.567 --> 00:07:15.970
My client was convinced
his wife was having an affair.

105
00:07:16.103 --> 00:07:17.939
maybe with the guy
that lives in this house.

106
00:07:18.072 --> 00:07:19.907
Thirty seconds
after she went inside.

107
00:07:20.041 --> 00:07:22.076
the place goes up in smoke?

108
00:07:22.209 --> 00:07:23.210
-What?
-Fine.

109
00:07:23.344 --> 00:07:25.112
-What?
-Oh. you think what?

110
00:07:25.246 --> 00:07:27.281
He rigged the house.
waited for you to confirm
she was here. and then what?

111
00:07:27.415 --> 00:07:28.783
It's possible.

112
00:07:28.916 --> 00:07:30.551
I mean. until now he seemed
like nothing but a nice guy.

113
00:07:30.685 --> 00:07:32.920
but who knows?

114
00:07:34.622 --> 00:07:36.290
No. no. no. no. no!

115
00:07:37.558 --> 00:07:39.193
Sir. sir. you have
to stay back.

116
00:07:39.327 --> 00:07:41.996
This is my house.
Please. I need to find my wife.
Her name is Natalie.

117
00:07:42.129 --> 00:07:44.332
Detective Mel Abreu.
Are you Preston Howard?

118
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:46.567
Yes. I've been trying
to reach my wife. but I can't.

119
00:07:46.701 --> 00:07:47.768
Please tell me
she wasn't in there.

120
00:07:47.902 --> 00:07:50.104
Mr. Howard.
there was one fatality.

121
00:07:50.237 --> 00:07:52.940
But we have reason to believe
it was someone other
than your wife.

122
00:07:53.074 --> 00:07:55.009
You're saying somebody
other than Natalie?

123
00:07:55.142 --> 00:07:57.011
Mr. Howard.
d-do you know a Louise Vernon?

124
00:07:58.145 --> 00:08:01.148
Yeah. W-We go
to the same country club.

125
00:08:01.282 --> 00:08:03.851
Are-Are you saying
she was inside my house?
Did she do this?

126
00:08:03.985 --> 00:08:06.253
Any chance she was coming here
to meet you today?

127
00:08:07.588 --> 00:08:10.825
Me? Why? W-Why would she?

128
00:08:11.625 --> 00:08:13.427
Why isn't anybody
trying to find my wife?

129
00:08:13.561 --> 00:08:15.296
We'll find her.
Mr. Howard. But first.

130
00:08:15.429 --> 00:08:17.965
I know the fire marshal
has some questions
about your house.

131
00:08:19.533 --> 00:08:22.203
I can't believe it.
I can't believe
that Louise is gone.

132
00:08:22.336 --> 00:08:26.374
Bob. like I said.
the person who died. the body.
it hasn't been identified yet.

133
00:08:27.008 --> 00:08:30.745
But y-you said you saw her go
inside. Who else could it be?

134
00:08:31.312 --> 00:08:33.981
Mr. Vernon. have you ever been
inside the Howards' house?

135
00:08:34.548 --> 00:08:40.421
Uh. they hosted
a holiday cocktail thing
a few years ago. Why?

136
00:08:40.554 --> 00:08:46.193
Well. you called Mr. Decker
this morning. He told you he
saw Louise go inside. Then...

137
00:08:48.863 --> 00:08:50.097
You...

138
00:08:50.231 --> 00:08:53.502
You think that
I blew it up somehow?

139
00:08:53.634 --> 00:08:55.302
Are you insane?

140
00:08:55.436 --> 00:08:58.172
You did hire a PI
because you thought
your wife was cheating on you.

141
00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:02.309
I told you how much
I loved her. I told you
I wanted to fix things.

142
00:09:02.443 --> 00:09:04.011
Bob. I know. I know.

143
00:09:04.145 --> 00:09:06.080
Please. Just go.

144
00:09:09.518 --> 00:09:10.584
Thoughts?

145
00:09:11.052 --> 00:09:12.653
My gut says he didn't do it.

146
00:09:13.154 --> 00:09:14.422
And yet?

147
00:09:14.555 --> 00:09:16.590
And yet. jealous husband.
dead wife. I know.

148
00:09:16.724 --> 00:09:18.527
Two and two
almost always equal four.

149
00:09:18.659 --> 00:09:22.430
and yet the fire marshal's
preliminary take was
the explosion was accidental.

150
00:09:23.164 --> 00:09:25.099
And yet. Louise was up
to something this morning.

151
00:09:25.232 --> 00:09:27.101
The car rental. the wig.
the storage locker.

152
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:30.037
I repeat. two plus two almost
always equal four.

153
00:09:30.171 --> 00:09:31.739
Look. she was having an affair.

154
00:09:31.872 --> 00:09:33.741
She changed
her car and her appearance
to visit a neighborhood

155
00:09:33.874 --> 00:09:34.942
where she could
have been recognized.

156
00:09:35.076 --> 00:09:37.278
Her death? Act of God.
not act of Bob.

157
00:09:37.411 --> 00:09:39.213
Okay.

158
00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:41.682
Look. something's up
with the storage locker.
It was big.

159
00:09:41.816 --> 00:09:43.784
It's way too big
for a... for a wig
and a change of clothes.

160
00:09:43.918 --> 00:09:46.320
-I'm gonna check it out.
-Okay. You find something
that tells you

161
00:09:46.454 --> 00:09:48.255
that the explosion wasn't
an accident. you let me know.

162
00:09:48.389 --> 00:09:52.026
Meantime. I'm gonna go focus
on crimes I know were murders.

163
00:10:01.969 --> 00:10:03.671
Gotcha. Let's go.

164
00:10:51.252 --> 00:10:53.287
Just when I thought
my day couldn't get any worse.

165
00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:54.922
Louise?

166
00:10:55.055 --> 00:10:58.192
You chose
the wrong night to try
to rob a storage locker. pal.

167
00:11:03.497 --> 00:11:06.033
You honestly want me to believe
you're a private investigator?

168
00:11:06.167 --> 00:11:08.035
We can check
my website if you want.

169
00:11:08.169 --> 00:11:11.172
but I think we'd both
be better off trying to
get you to a hospital.

170
00:11:13.274 --> 00:11:17.646
Louise. your husband Bob
hired me because he thought
you might be having an affair.

171
00:11:17.778 --> 00:11:20.381
I love Bob. I would never.

172
00:11:20.515 --> 00:11:23.884
Louise. I believe you. I do.
and not just 'cause of the gun.

173
00:11:24.018 --> 00:11:26.521
I don't think you went
to Preston Howard's
for a nooner today.

174
00:11:26.655 --> 00:11:28.923
I think you were there
to rob the place.

175
00:11:29.056 --> 00:11:33.194
Look. my least favorite job
as a PI is tailing
cheating spouses.

176
00:11:33.327 --> 00:11:35.229
A close second
is asset retrieval.

177
00:11:35.362 --> 00:11:37.898
See. insurance companies
pay guys like me
to be on the lookout

178
00:11:38.032 --> 00:11:40.734
for stolen goods in pawn shops.
on the black market.

179
00:11:40.868 --> 00:11:45.039
I recognize that
from a bulletin one of
those companies emailed me.

180
00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:49.443
If I had to take a guess.
I'd say everything
in here is stolen.

181
00:11:50.211 --> 00:11:51.378
You'd be wrong.

182
00:11:51.979 --> 00:11:55.015
I bought this stuff
at swap meets.
cash transactions.

183
00:11:55.149 --> 00:11:58.052
If any of it is stolen.
news to me.

184
00:11:59.420 --> 00:12:00.454
Louise...

185
00:12:01.188 --> 00:12:02.389
Bob thinks you're dead.

186
00:12:03.357 --> 00:12:06.927
Now. I watched you go
inside the Howards' house.
I have pictures.

187
00:12:08.095 --> 00:12:11.832
I... I didn't mean to...
to not go home to Bob.

188
00:12:12.567 --> 00:12:15.102
-I only came here
to change my clothes.
-Okay.

189
00:12:15.836 --> 00:12:18.739
Well. if you're here.
who was inside the house
when it exploded?

190
00:12:18.872 --> 00:12:21.543
I smelled the gas
the second I got inside.

191
00:12:22.109 --> 00:12:23.377
but I don't know
why I kept going.

192
00:12:24.044 --> 00:12:25.012
And then I saw her.

193
00:12:25.145 --> 00:12:26.447
You-You saw who?
Who did you see?

194
00:12:26.581 --> 00:12:29.116
All that blood.
And the gas.

195
00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:32.920
I was so scared.
so I went out back.
and then I heard a boom.

196
00:12:33.053 --> 00:12:34.288
And then I went flying.

197
00:12:35.089 --> 00:12:36.490
It's okay.

198
00:12:37.224 --> 00:12:38.759
My favorite Dior jacket.

199
00:12:38.892 --> 00:12:40.761
-It's okay. Oh. Oh.
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
-And now it's ruined.

200
00:12:40.894 --> 00:12:44.231
Hey. hey. I got you. I got you.

201
00:12:45.132 --> 00:12:46.433
Sofia's asleep.

202
00:12:47.468 --> 00:12:48.769
That's nice.

203
00:12:48.902 --> 00:12:49.970
It is nice.

204
00:12:50.672 --> 00:12:53.807
Maybe even very nice. Hmm?

205
00:12:55.376 --> 00:12:57.746
- Her again? Seriously?
- What?

206
00:12:57.878 --> 00:12:59.913
Baby.

207
00:13:00.047 --> 00:13:01.949
I'm giving you
the steal home sign.

208
00:13:02.082 --> 00:13:04.151
and you're still looking
for dirt on Emi Ochoa.

209
00:13:04.285 --> 00:13:07.488
I'm not looking for dirt.
I'm just trying to understand.

210
00:13:07.988 --> 00:13:10.659
You and your ex-husband
are both into sexy Latinas.

211
00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:12.226
What is there to understand?

212
00:13:12.359 --> 00:13:14.629
I don't know.
maybe how stupid I feel.

213
00:13:15.329 --> 00:13:16.363
I mean.

214
00:13:16.997 --> 00:13:19.166
two years I've been carrying
all this guilt for not seeing

215
00:13:19.300 --> 00:13:21.969
how much R.J.
was struggling before
he'd beat up Lucas Ochoa.

216
00:13:22.102 --> 00:13:26.173
and now I find out
that he's friends. maybe
even friends with benefits.

217
00:13:26.307 --> 00:13:29.343
with a woman who's
actually directly responsible
for him going to prison.

218
00:13:29.476 --> 00:13:32.046
Well. you said he told you
she's trying to make amends.

219
00:13:32.614 --> 00:13:34.048
She found a case
for him. So what?

220
00:13:34.181 --> 00:13:36.016
So she's a fricking Ochoa.

221
00:13:37.217 --> 00:13:40.020
Her dad is like
a modern-day Boss Tweed.

222
00:13:40.154 --> 00:13:42.691
They could be setting R.J. up
to be their fall guy.

223
00:13:42.823 --> 00:13:46.493
One. I resent you
making a reference
to a guy you know I won't know.

224
00:13:46.628 --> 00:13:49.063
Two. are you sure
you're not just jealous?

225
00:13:49.196 --> 00:13:50.197
What? No.

226
00:13:50.331 --> 00:13:52.933
I mean. she's pretty hot.

227
00:13:54.536 --> 00:13:55.836
Baby...

228
00:13:56.705 --> 00:14:00.441
You didn't carry guilt
for two years because
you're stupid. okay?

229
00:14:00.575 --> 00:14:03.043
- You did it because
you have a big heart.

230
00:14:03.177 --> 00:14:07.281
But come on. Don't you ever
think maybe you're a little too
involved with your ex?

231
00:14:09.149 --> 00:14:10.184
What?

232
00:14:10.951 --> 00:14:12.019
R.J.

233
00:14:12.687 --> 00:14:15.889
Someone we thought died
in that explosion today
turned up alive.

234
00:14:16.023 --> 00:14:19.093
Says there's a storage locker
on 19th I have to get to ASAP.

235
00:14:22.996 --> 00:14:26.568
Remind me.
Which one of us is
too involved with my ex?

236
00:14:35.543 --> 00:14:36.745
Hey. you get the warrant?

237
00:14:36.877 --> 00:14:38.412
Yeah. a little while ago.

238
00:14:38.546 --> 00:14:41.281
It's like a fricking
pirate's cave in here.

239
00:14:41.415 --> 00:14:44.184
Jewelry. artwork.
designer gowns.

240
00:14:44.652 --> 00:14:47.888
Robbery division
already matched a bunch
of it to a string of burglaries

241
00:14:48.021 --> 00:14:49.791
that dates back
a couple of years.

242
00:14:49.923 --> 00:14:52.326
They've been
calling the suspect
the Bandit of Broward.

243
00:14:52.459 --> 00:14:54.995
Now. thanks to you.
they know it was Louise Vernon.

244
00:14:55.129 --> 00:14:56.463
How is she. by the way?

245
00:14:56.598 --> 00:14:58.899
Uh. she's okay. She got a piece
of shrapnel in her abdomen.

246
00:14:59.032 --> 00:15:01.503
Lucky for her.
it didn't hit any organs.

247
00:15:01.636 --> 00:15:03.270
Lucky for us.

248
00:15:03.404 --> 00:15:05.640
'Cause the burglaries
aren't the only thing
she has to answer for.

249
00:15:05.774 --> 00:15:07.374
<i>What do you mean?</i>

250
00:15:07.509 --> 00:15:10.344
Finally got an ID
on the body that was found
in the rubble yesterday.

251
00:15:10.477 --> 00:15:12.279
Our bandit may be a murderer.

252
00:15:13.213 --> 00:15:15.949
You're telling me
everything I bought at
those swap meets was stolen?

253
00:15:16.083 --> 00:15:18.185
Ms. Vernon. you honestly
expect us to believe

254
00:15:18.318 --> 00:15:20.287
that you got a Patek Philippe
watch at a swap meet?

255
00:15:20.421 --> 00:15:21.955
Yeah. Louise. we know your MO.

256
00:15:22.089 --> 00:15:24.559
You put on
a pair of sunglasses.
a wig. you rent a nice car.

257
00:15:24.692 --> 00:15:27.127
so it looks like you belong
in the neighborhoods
you're targeting.

258
00:15:27.261 --> 00:15:29.163
If anyone spots you.
you're what?

259
00:15:29.296 --> 00:15:31.465
A high-end real estate broker
going door-to-door?

260
00:15:31.599 --> 00:15:33.601
Natalie Howard. though.
she was a friend.

261
00:15:33.735 --> 00:15:35.603
She would've seen right through
a disguise like that.

262
00:15:35.737 --> 00:15:38.338
Yeah. so we talked to Preston.
her husband. yesterday.

263
00:15:38.472 --> 00:15:39.908
We told him
we had reason to believe

264
00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:42.276
the body they found
inside the house
wasn't his wife's.

265
00:15:42.409 --> 00:15:43.611
Only it was.

266
00:15:43.745 --> 00:15:45.780
Medical examiner confirmed it
this morning.

267
00:15:45.914 --> 00:15:48.583
just like he confirmed
it wasn't the explosion
that killed her.

268
00:15:48.716 --> 00:15:51.452
She was dead before that.
Blunt force trauma to the head.

269
00:15:51.586 --> 00:15:54.221
You broke in.
Natalie caught you by surprise.

270
00:15:54.923 --> 00:15:56.223
And there was a struggle.

271
00:15:56.758 --> 00:15:59.761
<i>And you caved her skull in.</i>
<i>and you filled</i>
<i>the place with gas.</i>

272
00:15:59.894 --> 00:16:01.529
<i>And then you left something</i>
<i>behind to ignite it.</i>

273
00:16:01.663 --> 00:16:04.599
Arson investigator thinks
it was a hair dryer. he felt.

274
00:16:04.732 --> 00:16:05.767
Please.

275
00:16:07.134 --> 00:16:08.703
You have to tell them.

276
00:16:12.272 --> 00:16:14.374
I did break
into the house yesterday.

277
00:16:15.476 --> 00:16:17.044
But Natalie was dead
when I got there.

278
00:16:17.177 --> 00:16:20.447
Okay. right. and you got
all this in your storage locker
at swap meets.

279
00:16:20.582 --> 00:16:22.282
I can prove to you
I didn't kill her.

280
00:16:22.416 --> 00:16:25.587
The glasses I was wearing.
they-they weren't just
a part of my disguise.

281
00:16:25.720 --> 00:16:28.756
They were smart glasses.
They recorded everything I saw.

282
00:16:36.631 --> 00:16:39.534
I still don't understand
why you filmed yourself
breaking into houses.

283
00:16:39.667 --> 00:16:41.235
Why do you like
to record us in bed?

284
00:16:41.368 --> 00:16:45.138
- It's. I don't know.
a thrill reliving it.

285
00:16:47.842 --> 00:16:48.877
Yeah.

286
00:16:56.918 --> 00:16:58.720
Hair dryer.
just like they thought.

287
00:17:03.156 --> 00:17:04.191
<i>Oh. my God.</i>

288
00:17:06.928 --> 00:17:10.197
You want me to confess
to a few burglaries? I will.

289
00:17:10.665 --> 00:17:12.567
But murder? No.

290
00:17:12.700 --> 00:17:14.334
Somebody else killed Natalie.

291
00:17:19.106 --> 00:17:21.174
Hey. Mel. Hey.

292
00:17:22.476 --> 00:17:24.244
Heard your client say he needed
to speak with you.

293
00:17:24.378 --> 00:17:27.414
Well. it turns out
he doesn't want me
off the case just yet.

294
00:17:27.549 --> 00:17:29.717
The case of "I think my wife
is fooling around on me"?

295
00:17:29.851 --> 00:17:31.819
'Cause that one's solved.
She isn't a cheater.
she's a burglar.

296
00:17:31.953 --> 00:17:35.557
Yeah. I-I know.
but he says he feels terrible
about what happened to Natalie.

297
00:17:35.690 --> 00:17:38.860
He wants to make sure the cops
find the... find the killer.

298
00:17:38.993 --> 00:17:43.932
Right. because where
would the FLPD be without
the help of low-rent PI's?

299
00:17:44.064 --> 00:17:47.669
Well. technically.
I'm a no-rent PI. but hey.
hey. hey. hey. remind me.

300
00:17:47.802 --> 00:17:49.504
who caught
the Bandit of Broward?

301
00:17:49.637 --> 00:17:52.339
Okay. we both know
you're gonna go talk
to Preston Howard right now.

302
00:17:52.472 --> 00:17:53.908
Dead wife.
you look at the husband.

303
00:17:54.042 --> 00:17:56.410
You gotta talk to him.
I gotta talk to him.

304
00:17:56.544 --> 00:17:59.146
Why don't we. uh. save some
time. we'll do it together?

305
00:17:59.714 --> 00:18:02.717
We told Preston he could stay
with us as long as he needs.

306
00:18:02.850 --> 00:18:07.055
I can't even imagine
losing your home and
your wife all in an instant.

307
00:18:07.187 --> 00:18:10.290
Grant's been out there with him
all morning. but it's so hard.

308
00:18:10.424 --> 00:18:12.125
Neither of us knows
what to say.

309
00:18:12.627 --> 00:18:14.161
You've known
the Howards a long time?

310
00:18:14.294 --> 00:18:15.830
God. 15 years?

311
00:18:16.296 --> 00:18:18.298
I-I know it's none
of my business.

312
00:18:18.432 --> 00:18:22.135
but if you're here to confirm
the stove was the source
of the leak. be gentle.

313
00:18:22.269 --> 00:18:25.205
He told us
he's been meaning to replace
that old gas range for years.

314
00:18:25.339 --> 00:18:27.274
Well. actually. Ms. Summers.
we're here to tell him

315
00:18:27.407 --> 00:18:30.011
that that old gas stove
wasn't the cause
of Natalie's death.

316
00:18:30.578 --> 00:18:33.781
Oh. my God. Well. he'll be...
he'll be so relieved.

317
00:18:35.049 --> 00:18:36.884
Not so sure he will.

318
00:18:38.218 --> 00:18:41.121
You're saying
what happened to Natalie
wasn't an accident?

319
00:18:41.254 --> 00:18:42.757
You're saying that
she was murdered?

320
00:18:42.890 --> 00:18:45.459
The ME believes that.
based off the skull fracture.

321
00:18:45.593 --> 00:18:48.529
the weapon was something heavy
and rounded. like a pipe.

322
00:18:48.663 --> 00:18:51.498
Killer only set the explosion
to cover their tracks.

323
00:18:53.467 --> 00:18:55.903
You asked me
about Louise Vernon yesterday.

324
00:18:56.037 --> 00:18:57.270
It sounded like
she had been by the house.

325
00:18:57.404 --> 00:18:58.706
Yeah. 'cause she had.

326
00:18:58.840 --> 00:19:00.842
But as it turns out.
she wasn't there
to hurt anyone.

327
00:19:00.975 --> 00:19:02.476
She was there to rob the place.

328
00:19:02.610 --> 00:19:03.711
I'm not sure the FLPD was ready

329
00:19:03.845 --> 00:19:05.647
to share
that particular detail.

330
00:19:06.213 --> 00:19:08.348
But... yes. it's true.

331
00:19:08.482 --> 00:19:11.586
We like Louise Vernon
for a series of robberies
in this part of town.

332
00:19:11.719 --> 00:19:14.589
-Hold up. We were
robbed last year.
-Yeah.

333
00:19:14.722 --> 00:19:17.725
So were two other houses
on the street. Are you saying
that she was the one who--

334
00:19:17.859 --> 00:19:20.394
Probably. but-but it's not
what we're here for.

335
00:19:20.528 --> 00:19:22.997
and we were able
to prove Louise
didn't kill Natalie.

336
00:19:23.131 --> 00:19:27.200
So. Mr. Howard. can you
think of anybody else who
may have wanted to hurt her?

337
00:19:27.935 --> 00:19:31.204
No one. I mean.
Natalie was a saint.

338
00:19:31.939 --> 00:19:33.908
And things
were good with you guys?

339
00:19:35.043 --> 00:19:36.410
What do you mean?

340
00:19:36.544 --> 00:19:39.179
Your marriage.
No bumps in the road.
nothing like that?

341
00:19:41.516 --> 00:19:43.216
Y-You think that
I killed my wife?

342
00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:46.054
-Just routine questions.
Mr. Howard.
-The hell they are.

343
00:19:46.219 --> 00:19:48.422
You don't say another word.
not without an attorney.

344
00:19:48.556 --> 00:19:51.191
Okay. all we're trying to do
is eliminate Mr. Howard
as a suspect.

345
00:19:51.324 --> 00:19:53.861
Yeah. well. sorry.
You're not gonna do that here.

346
00:19:57.799 --> 00:19:59.534
That Grant's
a real charmer. huh?

347
00:20:00.168 --> 00:20:01.502
Yeah. humble too.

348
00:20:02.369 --> 00:20:05.338
Really puts the conspicuous
in conspicuous consumption.
doesn't it?

349
00:20:05.472 --> 00:20:06.607
Detective Abreu?

350
00:20:07.240 --> 00:20:10.545
I'm so sorry. I-I didn't want
to say anything
in front of Preston.

351
00:20:10.678 --> 00:20:14.515
but there was some trouble
in their marriage.

352
00:20:15.183 --> 00:20:17.051
Not that I think
he would ever hurt Natalie.

353
00:20:17.185 --> 00:20:20.688
but I just wouldn't
want you to find out later
that we'd held anything back.

354
00:20:20.822 --> 00:20:22.123
What kind of trouble?

355
00:20:22.255 --> 00:20:25.392
Preston asked Grant
for a loan a few weeks ago.

356
00:20:25.526 --> 00:20:28.563
Something about Natalie
spending too much.

357
00:20:29.163 --> 00:20:31.398
That's... That's all I know.

358
00:20:33.868 --> 00:20:35.036
<i>Imagine my surprise.</i>

359
00:20:36.037 --> 00:20:39.774
You reaching out
in the middle of the day.
saying you'd like to meet.

360
00:20:39.907 --> 00:20:41.542
In public. no less.

361
00:20:42.342 --> 00:20:43.611
What do you mean?

362
00:20:43.745 --> 00:20:45.312
Well. I mean.

363
00:20:45.445 --> 00:20:50.250
your newspaper
hasn't exactly been kind
to my family over the years.

364
00:20:51.519 --> 00:20:52.754
Not sure what your readers
would think

365
00:20:52.887 --> 00:20:56.724
if they saw us having coffee
together. Ms. Delacroix.

366
00:20:56.858 --> 00:20:58.458
First. it's Catherine.

367
00:20:58.593 --> 00:21:01.428
Second. I don't think
our readers would be
the least bit surprised.

368
00:21:01.562 --> 00:21:04.632
They know
<i>The Broward County Herald's</i>
only ever after the facts.

369
00:21:04.766 --> 00:21:06.433
Not sure my father would agree.

370
00:21:06.567 --> 00:21:09.971
but it's nice to finally
put a face to the byline.

371
00:21:10.705 --> 00:21:13.941
My assistant said you had
some questions about Ed Carter.

372
00:21:14.407 --> 00:21:16.443
For decades. he oversaw
one of the biggest chains

373
00:21:16.577 --> 00:21:18.179
of drug rehab clinics
in the state.

374
00:21:18.311 --> 00:21:21.015
Now he stands accused of
defrauding thousands of clients

375
00:21:21.149 --> 00:21:23.151
and orchestrating the death
of his own son.

376
00:21:23.283 --> 00:21:26.854
It's no secret
he's always been one of
your father's biggest donors.

377
00:21:26.988 --> 00:21:30.390
Just like it's no secret that
in light of those allegations.

378
00:21:30.525 --> 00:21:33.326
my father returned Mr. Carter's
most recent donation.

379
00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:35.763
and introduced legislation

380
00:21:35.897 --> 00:21:38.199
to increase
funding and oversight
for addiction treatment.

381
00:21:38.331 --> 00:21:41.269
It's my understanding
you played a big part
in bringing Ed Carter down.

382
00:21:41.401 --> 00:21:44.105
You-You worked
with a private investigator to
tee him up for law enforcement.

383
00:21:44.238 --> 00:21:47.440
I'm afraid that because
the investigation is ongoing.

384
00:21:47.575 --> 00:21:49.977
I can't comment on that
at this time.

385
00:21:50.111 --> 00:21:51.245
Huh.

386
00:21:51.378 --> 00:21:53.614
What about the PI?
Is he allowed to comment?

387
00:21:54.081 --> 00:21:56.449
I understand
he has some interesting ties
to your family too.

388
00:21:56.584 --> 00:21:58.186
your-your stepbrother
in particular.

389
00:22:03.124 --> 00:22:05.693
Sort of a no-no
when you've agreed
to an interview.

390
00:22:05.827 --> 00:22:07.427
Is that what this is?

391
00:22:07.995 --> 00:22:09.096
An interview?

392
00:22:10.363 --> 00:22:13.968
Because it seems
more like an invasion
of your ex-husband's privacy.

393
00:22:14.434 --> 00:22:17.205
God. after he did
what he did to Lucas.
you think we didn't find out

394
00:22:17.337 --> 00:22:19.006
every little thing
we could about him?

395
00:22:19.140 --> 00:22:20.675
I think you mean
what Lucas did to R.J.

396
00:22:20.808 --> 00:22:22.475
He was the one
who committed a crime that day.

397
00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:24.245
but R.J. went to prison.
thanks in no small part

398
00:22:24.377 --> 00:22:26.346
to the testimony
you gave at his trial.

399
00:22:26.479 --> 00:22:31.484
I take it you don't like
that I've been in R.J.'s orbit.

400
00:22:31.619 --> 00:22:35.556
but did it ever occur
to you that I genuinely
want to help him?

401
00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:37.424
If you want to help him...

402
00:22:38.292 --> 00:22:40.061
...maybe you'd like
to take this opportunity

403
00:22:40.194 --> 00:22:43.698
to admit on the record
that you perjured yourself
two years ago.

404
00:22:45.333 --> 00:22:47.835
Of course. that might mean
a little prison time for you.

405
00:22:49.871 --> 00:22:52.740
It's been a pleasure.
Ms. Delacroix.

406
00:22:57.912 --> 00:22:58.946
Same.

407
00:22:59.080 --> 00:23:01.082
Thanks.
You've been a big help.

408
00:23:02.850 --> 00:23:05.853
Million-dollar
life insurance policy
on his recently deceased wife

409
00:23:05.987 --> 00:23:09.790
plus the 2.5 from the house.
assuming that was insured too.

410
00:23:09.924 --> 00:23:11.759
Preston Howard's
money troubles are over.

411
00:23:11.893 --> 00:23:14.061
Between the windfall
and the attention
this case is getting.

412
00:23:14.195 --> 00:23:17.198
he's gonna
have lawyers lining up
to represent him. Good ones.

413
00:23:17.331 --> 00:23:20.902
Hope you got a good look
at him today 'cause we won't
see him again for a while.

414
00:23:21.035 --> 00:23:22.536
I bet you 50 bucks
you're wrong.

415
00:23:25.506 --> 00:23:28.743
I'm sorry for the way
that Grant spoke to you.

416
00:23:28.876 --> 00:23:32.380
He wasn't wrong.
A lawyer would make
a lot of sense.

417
00:23:33.881 --> 00:23:36.684
More importantly.
I think I might know
who killed Natalie.

418
00:23:38.386 --> 00:23:40.688
We're all ears. Mr. Howard.

419
00:23:40.821 --> 00:23:43.724
Look. I-I've never
paid much attention
to our finances.

420
00:23:44.225 --> 00:23:46.093
Natalie always took care
of the bills.

421
00:23:47.161 --> 00:23:49.130
About a month ago.
I noticed that the balance

422
00:23:49.263 --> 00:23:51.565
in our joint savings.
it seemed low.

423
00:23:52.533 --> 00:23:56.570
When I looked into it.
I saw that she had been making
some big cash withdrawals

424
00:23:56.704 --> 00:24:01.008
every month going
back almost a year.
Always just under $10.000.

425
00:24:01.142 --> 00:24:03.978
10K being the threshold
for reporting to the IRS.

426
00:24:04.912 --> 00:24:07.381
She said that it had
to be some kind of mistake

427
00:24:07.515 --> 00:24:09.250
and that she would look
into it. but...

428
00:24:10.651 --> 00:24:13.854
she seemed...
she seemed afraid.

429
00:24:14.922 --> 00:24:16.357
And I was worried.

430
00:24:17.892 --> 00:24:21.429
So the next time that she said
she had errands to run.
I-I followed her.

431
00:24:22.196 --> 00:24:23.998
She went to the bank.
made a cash withdrawal.

432
00:24:24.131 --> 00:24:25.433
and she drove straight
to Dixie Court.

433
00:24:25.566 --> 00:24:26.901
That's a rough area.

434
00:24:27.034 --> 00:24:30.504
She gave the money to a guy
that I'd never seen before.

435
00:24:31.238 --> 00:24:34.542
Tattoos everywhere. uh.
even on his face.

436
00:24:35.142 --> 00:24:37.645
And when she got home.
I asked her point blank.

437
00:24:37.778 --> 00:24:40.281
"Are you buying drugs?
Are you gambling?"

438
00:24:41.449 --> 00:24:42.984
She wouldn't tell me.

439
00:24:43.818 --> 00:24:45.553
She just said that
it was the last time.

440
00:24:45.686 --> 00:24:49.957
I told her. "Look.
whatever's going on. it's okay.
We can go to the police."

441
00:24:50.624 --> 00:24:54.095
She said that she was planning
to go herself.

442
00:24:55.730 --> 00:24:57.865
She just said that
she needed more time.

443
00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:02.303
Whatever Natalie got herself
into. I don't know.

444
00:25:03.304 --> 00:25:06.640
But maybe this guy wasn't okay.
her putting an end to it.

445
00:25:08.943 --> 00:25:11.979
Well. can you tell us
exactly where you saw
Natalie meet with him?

446
00:25:13.681 --> 00:25:14.715
Yeah.

447
00:25:22.456 --> 00:25:24.825
-Crockett or Tubbs?
-Hmm?

448
00:25:25.493 --> 00:25:26.861
Who's your favorite?

449
00:25:27.862 --> 00:25:29.930
Like. chocolate or vanilla?

450
00:25:30.064 --> 00:25:34.568
The Beatles or the Stones?
Crockett or Tubbs?

451
00:25:34.702 --> 00:25:36.237
Tubs of what?

452
00:25:38.706 --> 00:25:42.643
Are you really gonna sit there
and pretend you don't know
the guys from <i>Miami Vice?</i>

453
00:25:42.777 --> 00:25:44.612
I know the guys from
Fort Lauderdale Vice.

454
00:25:44.745 --> 00:25:48.549
I'm talking about
the TV show. the one...
You know what? Forget it.

455
00:25:48.682 --> 00:25:50.384
You are a terrible
stakeout partner.

456
00:25:50.519 --> 00:25:53.522
Why don't you call Emi Ochoa?
Ask her to tag me out.

457
00:25:55.289 --> 00:25:56.924
Catherine told you about that?

458
00:25:57.058 --> 00:25:59.860
Listen. don't get me wrong.
if I were single...

459
00:26:02.897 --> 00:26:04.131
-What?
-Over there.

460
00:26:04.265 --> 00:26:06.834
You think that's the guy
Natalie Howard was paying off?

461
00:26:07.735 --> 00:26:09.270
One way to find out.

462
00:26:13.874 --> 00:26:16.377
When I heard on the news
about a house blown up
in the suburbs.

463
00:26:17.278 --> 00:26:19.713
man. I had no idea
it was Mrs. H's.

464
00:26:21.182 --> 00:26:24.351
Well. we have pictures
of her too. if you'd like
to see them. Andre.

465
00:26:24.485 --> 00:26:26.020
I get why you brought me here.

466
00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:29.390
A nice white lady
coming to see a guy
with his face all tatted up.

467
00:26:29.524 --> 00:26:31.759
Oh. God. You're not here
because of the ink
on your face.

468
00:26:31.892 --> 00:26:33.562
You're here because of the ink
on your rap sheet.

469
00:26:33.694 --> 00:26:35.796
You got eight arrests
for possession of
a controlled substance.

470
00:26:35.930 --> 00:26:38.199
11 more for possession
with intent to distribute.

471
00:26:38.332 --> 00:26:41.035
I was a dealer.
Emphasis on "was".

472
00:26:41.168 --> 00:26:43.604
So if we were to test
what's left of "Mrs. H".

473
00:26:43.737 --> 00:26:45.339
we wouldn't find any drugs
in her system?

474
00:26:45.473 --> 00:26:48.776
No. I left all that behind. I
work as a youth counselor now.

475
00:26:48.909 --> 00:26:51.979
So then how do you explain
all that money Natalie Howard
was bringing you then?

476
00:26:52.113 --> 00:26:54.281
It's for a community center
I'm helping get built.

477
00:26:54.415 --> 00:26:57.485
The construction site
you picked me up at.
that's where it's going to be.

478
00:26:57.618 --> 00:27:02.356
Named for my baby brother.
Amari. He's the reason
me and Mrs. H met.

479
00:27:02.490 --> 00:27:03.691
And how do
they know each other?

480
00:27:03.824 --> 00:27:05.326
Actually. they didn't.

481
00:27:06.627 --> 00:27:09.797
He died last year. Hit-and-run.

482
00:27:10.764 --> 00:27:12.166
The story made
a lot of the papers.

483
00:27:12.299 --> 00:27:14.603
'cause he had just got
a full ride to Miami.

484
00:27:16.137 --> 00:27:17.805
That boy could hoop.

485
00:27:17.938 --> 00:27:21.709
But whoever ran him down
didn't give a damn who he was.

486
00:27:21.842 --> 00:27:23.410
Left him there to die.

487
00:27:23.545 --> 00:27:26.180
Mrs. H showed up
at the funeral. told my mom
she read about it.

488
00:27:26.313 --> 00:27:27.748
said she knew what
we were going through

489
00:27:27.882 --> 00:27:29.917
because she lost her son
to a drunk driver.

490
00:27:30.050 --> 00:27:32.186
When I told her I was trying to
get a community center built.

491
00:27:32.319 --> 00:27:35.689
name it after Amari.
she pledged a hundred grand.

492
00:27:35.823 --> 00:27:38.792
People donating
that amount don't tend
to do it in cash.

493
00:27:38.926 --> 00:27:41.328
They write checks.
They want the tax deductions.

494
00:27:41.462 --> 00:27:43.964
Honestly. I thought it was
a little sus too.

495
00:27:44.765 --> 00:27:46.467
She said she wanted
to be anonymous.

496
00:27:47.067 --> 00:27:49.638
that the only person who
deserved any attention
was Amari.

497
00:27:50.471 --> 00:27:53.307
Can you account for
your whereabouts on Tuesday
between 10:00 a.m. and noon?

498
00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:56.545
I can. So can a couple hundred
other people.

499
00:27:56.677 --> 00:28:00.848
I was at Mercer Elementary
School giving a talk about
staying away from drugs.

500
00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:08.189
Okay. let's just say everything
he told us was on the level.

501
00:28:08.322 --> 00:28:10.958
Natalie Howard was taking
money out for good reason.

502
00:28:11.091 --> 00:28:14.028
When Preston Howard
found out about it. why not
just tell him the truth?

503
00:28:14.161 --> 00:28:15.462
I'll do you one better.

504
00:28:15.597 --> 00:28:16.897
Why did she tell him
she was planning

505
00:28:17.031 --> 00:28:18.199
to go to the police?

506
00:28:18.332 --> 00:28:19.366
One sec.

507
00:28:21.168 --> 00:28:24.338
-Hey. what's up?
-Am I catching you
at a bad time?

508
00:28:24.471 --> 00:28:27.208
<i>No. it's</i> <i>a good time actually.
 I just</i> <i>got out of an interrogation.</i>

509
00:28:27.341 --> 00:28:28.876
Funny.

510
00:28:29.009 --> 00:28:31.646
I'm calling because
I went through one
of those myself today.

511
00:28:41.188 --> 00:28:42.657
Hey.

512
00:28:42.790 --> 00:28:45.226
Hey. how was your day?
You get up to anything
interesting?

513
00:28:45.359 --> 00:28:47.562
<i>I did. actually.</i>

514
00:28:47.696 --> 00:28:51.031
I'm doing a story on
that big win you had.
the Ed Carter thing.

515
00:28:51.165 --> 00:28:54.101
I thought I should
have a conversation
with Emi Ochoa.

516
00:28:54.235 --> 00:28:56.303
<i>Oh. really? Funny.</i>
<i>You didn't mention</i>
<i>that story to me.</i>

517
00:28:56.437 --> 00:28:58.872
Oh. I'm sorry.
Are we keeping score now

518
00:28:59.006 --> 00:29:01.175
when it comes to things one
of us didn't tell the other?

519
00:29:01.308 --> 00:29:03.244
<i>I get what you like about her.</i>
<i>by the way.</i>

520
00:29:03.377 --> 00:29:05.045
<i>I mean. her capacity</i>
<i>for forgiveness.</i>

521
00:29:05.179 --> 00:29:07.616
her willingness to get
into bed figuratively.
of course.

522
00:29:07.748 --> 00:29:12.152
with the meth addict who
tried to kill her brother for.
you know. no reason at all.

523
00:29:12.286 --> 00:29:14.288
I mean. people have been
sainted for less.

524
00:29:14.421 --> 00:29:17.626
I told you. okay? I told you.
She regrets what she did.

525
00:29:18.192 --> 00:29:20.629
I'm glad that's enough for you.
It isn't for me.

526
00:29:25.466 --> 00:29:26.800
-Found something.
Assuming you're done...
-Yeah.

527
00:29:26.934 --> 00:29:28.637
-...with your personal calls?
-Sorry.

528
00:29:29.604 --> 00:29:31.805
What did Catherine do now?

529
00:29:31.939 --> 00:29:36.844
Listen. you are. for all
your faults. one of the coolest
customers I've ever met.

530
00:29:36.977 --> 00:29:41.081
Nothing ever seems
to bother you except for when
my wife calls you on your BS.

531
00:29:41.215 --> 00:29:44.084
I'm gonna go on a limb and say
it has something to do
with Emi Ochoa.

532
00:29:44.218 --> 00:29:47.454
Let's just say
Catherine decided
to introduce herself today.

533
00:29:47.589 --> 00:29:49.390
and we'll just...
we'll just leave it at that.

534
00:29:49.957 --> 00:29:51.258
Oh. man.

535
00:29:52.627 --> 00:29:56.130
Did I ever tell you
about the day you
were sentenced.

536
00:29:56.263 --> 00:29:58.633
-what Catherine did?
-Mm-mmm.

537
00:29:58.767 --> 00:30:02.469
Went home. got in bed.
and didn't get out
for three days.

538
00:30:02.604 --> 00:30:05.939
I remember thinking like.
"Hey. what the hell?
This is her ex."

539
00:30:06.073 --> 00:30:08.108
You know. most people.
they hear their ex
is going to prison.

540
00:30:08.242 --> 00:30:11.513
they throw a party.
and I will admit that. like.
for a millisecond

541
00:30:11.646 --> 00:30:13.380
I thought maybe
she wasn't over you.

542
00:30:13.515 --> 00:30:18.052
And then I realized.
oh. my beautiful wife.
your beautiful ex.

543
00:30:19.053 --> 00:30:22.289
she just loves bigger
than I understood.

544
00:30:23.157 --> 00:30:25.826
And when you love that big.
you worry that big.

545
00:30:26.827 --> 00:30:30.565
My question for you is.
do you love being loved big?

546
00:30:31.666 --> 00:30:33.133
Because if you don't...

547
00:30:40.374 --> 00:30:43.010
-You said you had something.
-Yeah.

548
00:30:46.347 --> 00:30:48.115
Everything Andre Blake told us
checked out.

549
00:30:48.248 --> 00:30:50.384
He was at that school the day
the Howards' house blew up.

550
00:30:50.518 --> 00:30:53.120
and his brother was killed
in a hit-and-run last year.

551
00:30:54.221 --> 00:30:57.358
Okay. so as far as suspects go.
we're back to square one.

552
00:30:57.491 --> 00:30:59.193
Mmm. In the death
of Natalie Howard. yes.

553
00:30:59.326 --> 00:31:01.696
In the death of baby bro.
not so much.

554
00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:05.466
Natalie Howard never had a kid.
let alone one killed
by a drunk driver.

555
00:31:05.600 --> 00:31:08.737
So I wondered. why show up
at Amari Blake's funeral?

556
00:31:08.869 --> 00:31:13.742
Why pledge a hundred grand
to a community center being
built in his honor?

557
00:31:13.874 --> 00:31:16.511
Let me guess.
once Natalie's death
was ruled a homicide.

558
00:31:16.644 --> 00:31:18.312
you got access
to her phone records.

559
00:31:18.445 --> 00:31:19.614
Way ahead of you.

560
00:31:19.748 --> 00:31:21.181
The night Amari Blake died
in that hit-and-run.

561
00:31:21.315 --> 00:31:23.685
guess whose phone was pinging
off the nearest tower?

562
00:31:24.853 --> 00:31:27.622
<i>Okay. so</i>
<i>if Natalie Howard killed Amari.</i>

563
00:31:27.756 --> 00:31:29.923
but Amari's brother
didn't kill Natalie.

564
00:31:30.057 --> 00:31:32.694
then maybe one of the family
members found out the truth

565
00:31:32.827 --> 00:31:35.162
and killed her to get revenge.

566
00:31:37.799 --> 00:31:40.000
Sorry. it's my client.
I'm sorry.

567
00:31:40.134 --> 00:31:43.270
-Hey. Bob. What's up?
You need an update?
-No. I just got home.

568
00:31:43.404 --> 00:31:45.874
Someone must have broken in.
Everything is torn apart.

569
00:31:46.006 --> 00:31:50.444
I didn't want to call the
police because of everything
going on with Louise. but...

570
00:31:50.578 --> 00:31:52.346
<i>Okay. Bob. take a deep breath.</i>

571
00:31:52.479 --> 00:31:54.248
<i>Just get out of the house.</i>
<i>I'll be there in like--</i>

572
00:31:54.381 --> 00:31:57.552
I just heard
something. I think the person
who did this may--

573
00:31:57.685 --> 00:32:00.954
Bob. Bob. what was that?

574
00:32:02.724 --> 00:32:04.425
<i>Bob. answer. What was it? Bob?</i>

575
00:32:13.033 --> 00:32:16.236
Paramedics say he'll make it.
but the blow was to
the back of the head.

576
00:32:16.370 --> 00:32:17.839
Odds are he didn't see
who did it.

577
00:32:17.971 --> 00:32:20.708
Blow to the back of the head.
just like Natalie Howard.

578
00:32:20.842 --> 00:32:22.476
You think the guy
who killed her did this?

579
00:32:22.610 --> 00:32:24.278
I mean. as far
as signatures go.

580
00:32:24.411 --> 00:32:26.980
hitting people on the head
is not a very unique one.

581
00:32:27.114 --> 00:32:30.184
And if you're right.
what motive would they have
for attacking them both?

582
00:32:30.317 --> 00:32:34.121
Well. any luck.
the answer's going to come
from that guy right there.

583
00:32:34.254 --> 00:32:35.989
Mr. Adult Onesie?

584
00:32:36.123 --> 00:32:39.594
Actually. Mr. Ring Camera.
He just told me his has
a great view of Bob's driveway.

585
00:32:43.363 --> 00:32:45.499
Hey. are you seriously using

586
00:32:45.633 --> 00:32:46.768
terry cloth again?

587
00:32:46.901 --> 00:32:49.604
How many times have I told you.
microfiber only?

588
00:32:56.644 --> 00:32:59.179
Hey. if you're looking
for Preston. he isn't here.

589
00:32:59.313 --> 00:33:01.616
He had to go make
some funeral arrangements
for Natalie.

590
00:33:01.749 --> 00:33:05.219
Actually. Mr. Summers.
we're here for you.

591
00:33:06.086 --> 00:33:09.356
We have video
of this car arriving at
Bob Vernon's house just minutes

592
00:33:09.490 --> 00:33:11.291
before someone
assaulted him last night.

593
00:33:11.425 --> 00:33:13.260
There's lots of cars
like this out there.

594
00:33:13.393 --> 00:33:17.532
Yeah. But only one
Luxxguy1. right?

595
00:33:18.766 --> 00:33:19.834
Lawyer.

596
00:33:27.842 --> 00:33:29.644
This is what
you've been doing?

597
00:33:29.777 --> 00:33:33.146
Yeah. Well. complicated case.
I thought some visual aids
might help.

598
00:33:33.280 --> 00:33:35.182
Hmm. I'd say it looks
like something Sofia made.

599
00:33:35.315 --> 00:33:37.417
but I know
she can do better than this.

600
00:33:38.853 --> 00:33:41.154
Three couples. all friends
from the same country club.

601
00:33:41.288 --> 00:33:43.190
all connected by the murder
of Natalie Howard.

602
00:33:43.323 --> 00:33:46.093
And by the Bandit of Broward.
aka Louise Vernon.

603
00:33:46.226 --> 00:33:49.062
Exactly. She did rob
the Summers' house.

604
00:33:49.196 --> 00:33:51.566
She attempted to rob
the Howards' house.

605
00:33:52.032 --> 00:33:54.501
I think she's
the reason Grant went
to Bob's house last night.

606
00:33:55.135 --> 00:33:56.738
-Revenge?
-Asset retrieval.

607
00:33:56.871 --> 00:33:58.640
I told Louise it's
my least favorite job.

608
00:33:58.773 --> 00:34:01.408
but it's a thing for a reason.
Someone steals your stuff.
you want it back.

609
00:34:01.543 --> 00:34:04.579
Louise's storage locker
was a detail we kept
out of the press.

610
00:34:04.712 --> 00:34:07.281
Yes. exactly. That's why
I think Grant went to
her house last night.

611
00:34:07.414 --> 00:34:09.116
tore it up looking
for something she stole.

612
00:34:09.249 --> 00:34:12.152
Why wouldn't he
just contact the police? Ask
if his property was recovered?

613
00:34:12.286 --> 00:34:13.688
Well. you're assuming
what he was looking for.

614
00:34:13.821 --> 00:34:15.188
he'd be okay
with the police knowing about.

615
00:34:15.322 --> 00:34:16.758
What. like a brick
of cocaine or something?

616
00:34:16.891 --> 00:34:18.560
Spidey sense says no.

617
00:34:18.693 --> 00:34:20.929
but that's only because.
based on the items retrieved
from the storage locker.

618
00:34:21.061 --> 00:34:24.131
she wasn't into drugs.
only things that were nice.

619
00:34:24.264 --> 00:34:26.466
What nice thing would have
tied Grant to a crime?

620
00:34:26.601 --> 00:34:30.605
Don't know. but I gotta think
it's the same reason
he killed Natalie Howard.

621
00:34:30.738 --> 00:34:33.908
Lucky for us. we have a bandit
who can just tell us
what she stole.

622
00:34:35.677 --> 00:34:38.012
<i>You really think what happened</i>
<i>to Bob was my fault?</i>

623
00:34:38.145 --> 00:34:40.615
Well. we think
they're connected. Yeah.

624
00:34:42.884 --> 00:34:45.687
All this awfulness.

625
00:34:47.722 --> 00:34:50.592
Just because I was bored
and needed a little
excitement in my life.

626
00:34:51.926 --> 00:34:54.963
Bob's doctor said he opened
his eyes this morning.

627
00:34:56.531 --> 00:35:00.768
He didn't say anything.
but she thinks
it's a good sign.

628
00:35:00.902 --> 00:35:02.604
She thinks he's gonna be okay.

629
00:35:04.371 --> 00:35:07.107
That's... That's good.
Louise. I'm glad.

630
00:35:10.011 --> 00:35:11.913
You said this is the claim
Grant and Dawn filed

631
00:35:12.046 --> 00:35:13.781
with their insurance company
after I robbed them.

632
00:35:13.915 --> 00:35:17.250
but I'm still a little fuzzy
on what I'm supposed
to be looking for.

633
00:35:17.852 --> 00:35:19.319
Something that isn't there.

634
00:35:20.088 --> 00:35:23.290
The idea is you stole something
that could have gotten
Grant in trouble.

635
00:35:23.992 --> 00:35:27.260
and if you did.
there's a good chance he
wouldn't make a claim for it.

636
00:35:29.396 --> 00:35:32.165
- Like the dog
that doesn't bark. right?

637
00:35:32.299 --> 00:35:34.167
It's the absence
of things that matters.

638
00:35:34.301 --> 00:35:38.271
I'm guessing you stole
the complete works of
Sherlock Holmes at some point.

639
00:35:42.309 --> 00:35:43.578
Wow.

640
00:35:44.979 --> 00:35:47.147
I'm the one being
accused of theft?

641
00:35:47.280 --> 00:35:48.315
What do you mean?

642
00:35:48.916 --> 00:35:51.385
Grant and Dawn
have been ripping off
their insurance company.

643
00:35:54.022 --> 00:35:55.823
- Erté statuette.
- Yeah?

644
00:35:55.957 --> 00:35:58.291
Gucci dress. emerald brooch.

645
00:35:59.661 --> 00:36:04.331
They claimed at least
20.000 bucks' worth of stuff
that I definitely didn't take.

646
00:36:06.034 --> 00:36:10.004
Do you want
to charge him for fraud?
I'm willing to testify.

647
00:36:10.138 --> 00:36:12.372
Oh. yeah.
in exchange for reducing
the charges against you?

648
00:36:13.240 --> 00:36:14.374
Actually. I...

649
00:36:15.677 --> 00:36:18.211
I was hoping
I could get permission
to visit Bob's room.

650
00:36:18.946 --> 00:36:21.616
I-- I know I'm under arrest.

651
00:36:21.749 --> 00:36:24.986
but I'd like to hold his hand.

652
00:36:25.953 --> 00:36:27.889
maybe even be there
when he wakes up.

653
00:36:29.189 --> 00:36:32.093
You find something that proves
Grant Summers is a killer.

654
00:36:32.225 --> 00:36:34.162
and I'll work on that
and the charges.

655
00:36:39.266 --> 00:36:40.300
Huh.

656
00:36:41.334 --> 00:36:44.072
The most valuable thing I took
from Grant and Dawn's house.

657
00:36:44.204 --> 00:36:45.238
the one they could have made

658
00:36:45.372 --> 00:36:47.374
- a huge legitimate claim for...
- Mm-hmm.

659
00:36:48.341 --> 00:36:49.376
It's not listed here.

660
00:36:55.382 --> 00:36:57.384
There. right there.

661
00:36:58.351 --> 00:37:01.756
Ostrich skin
with 18-karat gold hardware.

662
00:37:01.889 --> 00:37:03.457
There were only six made.

663
00:37:03.591 --> 00:37:08.763
One of them was auctioned
at Sotheby's last year.
sold for over 200.000.

664
00:37:08.896 --> 00:37:10.665
Of course. I couldn't wear it.

665
00:37:10.798 --> 00:37:14.334
It would've attracted
too much attention. but it
sure was nice to look at.

666
00:37:14.468 --> 00:37:16.003
Okay. maybe Grant stole it.

667
00:37:16.137 --> 00:37:18.338
and didn't make a claim
because it would tie him
to the crime.

668
00:37:18.472 --> 00:37:21.274
A murder. an attempted murder.
and exploded a house
all for a stolen bag?

669
00:37:21.408 --> 00:37:23.945
-I don't think so.
-A stolen bag worth
over 200 grand.

670
00:37:24.078 --> 00:37:25.980
I don't think
it was the bag
he was looking for.

671
00:37:26.114 --> 00:37:28.482
It's what was inside the bag.

672
00:37:28.616 --> 00:37:29.951
Did you know that was in there?

673
00:37:30.084 --> 00:37:33.420
No. I told you I never used
the bag. and I don't get it.

674
00:37:33.554 --> 00:37:34.889
What's so special
about a license plate?

675
00:37:35.022 --> 00:37:37.091
Ordinarily not much.
but I think this one's going

676
00:37:37.225 --> 00:37:40.027
to prove one of
the Summers is a killer.

677
00:37:43.598 --> 00:37:49.070
Mrs. Summers.
do you recognize these?

678
00:37:50.538 --> 00:37:54.876
Of course. they were all stolen
from my home. but I'm confused.

679
00:37:55.009 --> 00:37:59.279
Is that why
you asked me to come here.
to give them back to me?

680
00:38:00.214 --> 00:38:03.785
Because I thought
you had questions about
the little misunderstanding

681
00:38:03.918 --> 00:38:05.586
between Grant and Bob Vernon.

682
00:38:05.720 --> 00:38:08.122
You mean when
Grant misunderstood a pipe
to the back of Bob's skull?

683
00:38:09.190 --> 00:38:12.727
Grant went there to talk to Bob
about what Louise had done.

684
00:38:12.860 --> 00:38:16.097
Things got heated
and Bob came at him.

685
00:38:16.230 --> 00:38:18.398
-Mmm.
-Grant was just
defending himself.

686
00:38:19.734 --> 00:38:21.434
What about this?

687
00:38:22.369 --> 00:38:23.436
Recognize this?

688
00:38:24.772 --> 00:38:26.306
No. that isn't mine.

689
00:38:27.508 --> 00:38:30.211
You sure? Because a bag
like that is easy to trace.

690
00:38:30.812 --> 00:38:33.981
Your husband
got it at auction a year ago.
just before your 50th birthday.

691
00:38:34.115 --> 00:38:39.787
which. according to
social media posts. you
celebrated at Cabrera in Miami.

692
00:38:42.957 --> 00:38:46.594
Yes. sorry.
I... I remember now.

693
00:38:46.727 --> 00:38:51.299
I have so many bags.
I suppose I just...
I forgot about this one.

694
00:38:51.431 --> 00:38:54.802
That must be nice to be
so rich you could forget about
one that costs six figures.

695
00:38:54.936 --> 00:38:58.506
What about this?
Recognize that?

696
00:38:59.173 --> 00:39:04.212
That appears to be a plate
from a car I reported
stolen last year.

697
00:39:04.344 --> 00:39:06.814
Well. not just last year.
the day after
your birthday party.

698
00:39:08.115 --> 00:39:10.483
I'm confused.
Did you find the car?

699
00:39:10.618 --> 00:39:14.387
No. odds are we never will
because odds are
you and Grant got rid of it.

700
00:39:14.522 --> 00:39:16.356
That's crazy.
Why would we do that?

701
00:39:16.489 --> 00:39:20.294
Because it was your car
that struck and killed a kid
named Amari Blake last year.

702
00:39:22.296 --> 00:39:24.397
<i>At first we thought</i>
<i>it was Natalie who did it.</i>

703
00:39:24.532 --> 00:39:26.901
<i>but. no. she was just</i>
<i>a passenger. wasn't she?</i>

704
00:39:27.034 --> 00:39:32.106
We traced the chain of title
on the car. 1975 Mercedes SLC.

705
00:39:32.240 --> 00:39:33.608
It's a real classic.

706
00:39:33.741 --> 00:39:35.375
Originally purchased
by your father the week
you were born.

707
00:39:35.509 --> 00:39:38.112
he transferred the title
to you when you turned 16.

708
00:39:38.246 --> 00:39:40.413
and you could've
just gotten rid of the plate
along with the car.

709
00:39:40.548 --> 00:39:42.884
but it was more than just proof
of a crime. wasn't it?

710
00:39:46.888 --> 00:39:50.358
It was proof of
how much Daddy loved you
and how special you are.

711
00:39:50.490 --> 00:39:54.394
Yeah. so much more special
than some random
7-year-old on a bike.

712
00:39:56.063 --> 00:39:59.333
It's too bad Louise stole
your bag before you had
a chance to get this out.

713
00:40:01.035 --> 00:40:06.540
Obviously you managed
to swear Natalie to secrecy
that night. but unlike you.

714
00:40:06.674 --> 00:40:08.709
her conscience. it got to her.

715
00:40:09.610 --> 00:40:13.547
She ended up donating $100.000
to a community center
in Amari's name.

716
00:40:13.681 --> 00:40:16.250
Recently. she told her husband
there was something
she needed to tell him.

717
00:40:16.384 --> 00:40:19.419
and we think she
was going to spill about what
really happened that night.

718
00:40:19.553 --> 00:40:22.489
and we think she gave you
the opportunity to do the same.

719
00:40:22.623 --> 00:40:25.092
Instead. you sic
your psycho husband on her.

720
00:40:26.928 --> 00:40:30.064
No. no. Grant would never.

721
00:40:30.731 --> 00:40:33.301
-He's a good man.
-So good he wouldn't
take a plea deal

722
00:40:33.433 --> 00:40:35.336
to pin Amari and Natalie's
murder on you?

723
00:40:36.304 --> 00:40:39.340
Because you should know
the DA's office is about
to offer him one...

724
00:40:39.472 --> 00:40:40.942
in about 20 minutes.

725
00:40:41.809 --> 00:40:45.680
Unless. of course.
you want to talk about
a deal for yourself.

726
00:40:51.585 --> 00:40:54.288
Cath. Made it.

727
00:40:55.022 --> 00:40:57.258
You said in your text you had
a much better story for me

728
00:40:57.391 --> 00:41:00.561
than "Emi Ochoa dupes
Florida PI a second time."

729
00:41:00.695 --> 00:41:01.629
How could I resist?

730
00:41:01.762 --> 00:41:03.097
-Look. about that--
-It's okay.

731
00:41:04.732 --> 00:41:08.035
I overstepped.
Not a lot. but enough.

732
00:41:09.236 --> 00:41:10.972
-So still pals then. yeah?
-Well. it depends

733
00:41:11.105 --> 00:41:12.640
-how good this other story is.
-Well. actually

734
00:41:12.773 --> 00:41:14.308
-you have your choice of two.
-Mm-hmm.

735
00:41:14.442 --> 00:41:18.179
My client Bob Vernon.
husband of the infamous
Bandit of Broward.

736
00:41:18.312 --> 00:41:20.681
he hasn't talked
to the press since he got
out of the hospital.

737
00:41:20.815 --> 00:41:23.918
But for the wife of the cop
who just talked the DA
into a plea deal

738
00:41:24.051 --> 00:41:26.554
that would see her serve
less than a year?

739
00:41:27.221 --> 00:41:28.422
He'd make an exception.

740
00:41:28.589 --> 00:41:30.524
And behind door number two?

741
00:41:31.926 --> 00:41:33.361
You see that group over there?

742
00:41:34.996 --> 00:41:36.564
It's the family of Amari Blake.

743
00:41:37.264 --> 00:41:39.467
I just told them how
Dawn and Grant Summer.

744
00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:41.535
they couldn't turn
on each other fast enough.

745
00:41:42.269 --> 00:41:43.871
They're both probably going
to go away for life.

746
00:41:44.005 --> 00:41:45.906
Now it doesn't bring
Amari back.

747
00:41:46.040 --> 00:41:48.943
but they're all glad to be
finally getting some justice.

748
00:41:49.076 --> 00:41:51.545
Now. I figured a piece
in the <i>Herald</i> would be
a good way

749
00:41:51.679 --> 00:41:53.814
to remind people who he was.

750
00:41:53.948 --> 00:41:55.182
how much he was loved.

751
00:41:55.983 --> 00:41:59.687
Not to mention some good
publicity for the community
center they're building.

752
00:42:01.956 --> 00:42:03.691
You're really gonna
make me choose?

753
00:42:03.824 --> 00:42:05.326
Well. it depends.

754
00:42:05.459 --> 00:42:07.194
You're gonna quit
trying to make me go
on the dating apps?

755
00:42:07.328 --> 00:42:09.597
I'll let you know
after we talk to the Blakes.

756
00:42:11.232 --> 00:42:13.567
All right. let's talk
to the Blakes.
